#carousel-testimonial.carousel.slide{"data-ride" => "carousel"}
  / Indicators
  %ol.carousel-indicators
    -# %li.active{"data-slide-to" => "0", "data-target" => "#carousel-testimonial"}
    -# %li{"data-slide-to" => "1", "data-target" => "#carousel-testimonial"}
    = image_tag 'icons/person.normal.red.png', style: "height:30px; width: 30px; ", data: { "slide-to" => "0", target: "#carousel-testimonial"}, class: 'active'
    = image_tag 'icons/person.excited.blue.png', style: "height:30px; width: 30px; ", data: { "slide-to" => "1", target: "#carousel-testimonial"}
    = image_tag 'icons/person.normal.red.png', style: "height:30px; width: 30px; ", data: { "slide-to" => "2", target: "#carousel-testimonial"}

  / Wrapper for slides
  .carousel-inner{:role => "listbox"}
    #testimonial1.item.active
      .col-sm-8.col-sm-offset-4{ style: 'height: 100%; padding: 20px 80px;'}
        %p.lead.centered
          With the exception of a routine physical here and there, Laura had rarely needed medical care. She had aged off her parents’ insurance after her 25th birthday and was between jobs when she took a bad fall playing ultimate frisbee. She had broken a rib and collapsed a lung, which the doctors in the ER were able to fix with ease. However, she left the hospital with debt that will burden her for the better part of a decade.
    #testimonial3.item
      .col-sm-10.col-sm-offset-1{ style: 'height: 100%; padding: 20px 50px;'}
        %p.lead.centered
          Whether a young adult or a new American, living without health insurance means that every day is a gamble. Catastrophic medical expenses and bankruptcy are always just an injury or accident away. Most uninsured individuals know this. They know how precarious it is to be uninsured and want health insurance. They are, however, simply overwhelmed by the health care marketplace. What they need are helping hands and one-on-one conversations to help them make a well-informed decision about their health insurance options.  
    #testimonial2.item
      .col-sm-8{ style: 'height: 100%; padding: 20px 80px;'}
        %p.lead.centered
          Juan Carlos and his family had moved to New Jersey from El Salvador four years ago. His family, including his young son, had been blessed with good health. However, English wasn’t his first language and navigating the health care marketplace was complicated. As a result, he and his family were without insurance when they were rear-ended by an SUV on the Turnpike. The hospital staff nursed them back to full health but Juan Carlos wakes up every morning worried about making ends meet because of mounting medical bills.